/explain No inputs were found in config file 'c:/Users/Gustavo/Engenharia_Software_II_PLUS/plus-ms-auth/tsconfig.json'. Specified 'include' paths were '["src/**/*"]' and 'exclude' paths were '["node_modules","dist","tests"]'.

The error means tsc did not find any TypeScript input files under src/**/*.

Your tsconfig.json currently only includes:

"include": ["src/**/*"]
So TypeScript looks for .ts, .tsx, .js, etc. under src. If that folder does not exist or has no matching files, you get this error.

Possible fixes:

If your sources are in a different folder, update include accordingly. Example:
"include": ["src/**/*", "tests/**/*"]
If your project files are in the repo root instead of src, change it to:
"include": ["**/*"]
If this is a JS project and you want to compile JS too, add:
"allowJs": true

